From that story, lets now focus on Covid situation and it appears Kenya escaped the wrath of the predicted covid 19 fourth wave with the ministry of health attributing this to enhanced containment measures by government. This included cessation of movement imposed in 13 counties in the lake basin economic block. And as Gloria Milimu reports, a report by the KEMRI welcome trust had predicted a more lethal covid 19 fourth wave in mid July but this did not happen.
